<FeaturePage title="EDDI Manager" description="A production-ready React management UI for building, deploying, and monitoring AI agents visually — with 11-locale i18n, live chat debugging, and audit dashboards." heroImage={heroImage}>

<h2>Visual Agent Management</h2>
<p>The EDDI Manager is a comprehensive React-based management interface that provides visual control over every aspect of the EDDI platform — from agent configuration to real-time conversation monitoring.</p>

<h3>Key Capabilities</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Visual Agent Builder</strong> — Create and configure agents through an intuitive drag-and-drop interface</li>
<li><strong>Live Chat Debugging</strong> — Test agents in real-time with full conversation inspection</li>
<li><strong>Audit Dashboards</strong> — Monitor token usage, costs, and performance across all agents</li>
<li><strong>11-Locale i18n</strong> — Full internationalization with RTL support for Arabic</li>
<li><strong>Interactive Onboarding</strong> — Guided tours that introduce new users to the platform</li>
<li><strong>Resource Management</strong> — CRUD operations for rules, workflows, LLM configs, and connectors</li>
<li><strong>Secrets Vault</strong> — Secure API key management with masked display</li>
</ul>

<h3>Built for Teams</h3>
<p>The Manager enables non-developers to iterate on agent behavior without touching Java code. Prompt engineers can modify rules, test conversations, and deploy changes — all from the browser.</p>

</FeaturePage>

